#install virtual machine
1) sudo apt-get install virtualbox
2) New> Linux Ubuntu > use an existing HD > newVM.vdi
3) mandatory settings for Gazebo (remove 3d acceleration)
Settings>Displacy >Untick enable 3D acceleration
General>system> (8CPU /10Gbyte RAM memory /moniotor count 8 / 256Mb memory
4) General advanced>shared clipboard>bidirectional

OPTIONS:
# if you need to resize (on your VirtualBox folder in host machine) :
sudo VBoxManage modifymedium newVM.vdi --resize 30000

# to access shared OS foldeer
1) add foder to shared folders
2) install Devices->Install Guest Additions 
3)  sudo ./VBoxLinuxAdditions.run
4)  sudo mount -t vboxsf OS_HOME ~/Desktop/ubuntu-share
5) to permanently mount https://gist.github.com/estorgio/1d679f962e8209f8a9232f7593683265

#to have multiple monitors
In your VBox under "View > Virtual Screen 2" called "Enable" that will turn the screen on for you. That way you can get your second window for VirtualBox.

